ðŸ”¢ Numeric Formatting Types
Format	Meaning	Example (num = 255)
:d	Decimal (base 10)	255
:b	Binary (base 2)	11111111
:o	Octal (base 8)	377
:x	Hexadecimal (lowercase)	ff
:X	Hexadecimal (UPPERCASE)	FF
:n	Number with locale separator	255 or 255,000
:,	Adds comma as thousands separator	1,000,000
:_	Underscore as thousands separator	1_000_000
:e	Scientific notation (lowercase)	2.550000e+02
:E	Scientific notation (UPPERCASE)	2.550000E+02
:f	Fixed-point notation (floats)	255.000000
:.2f	Float with 2 decimal places	255.00
%	Percentage (multiplies by 100)	0.85 â†’ 85.000000%

ðŸ”§ Other format options (alignment, padding, signs)
Spec	Meaning	Example
>, <, ^  	Align right, left, center	f"{42:>5}" â†’ ' 42'
+  	Always show sign	+42, -42
(space)  	Leading space for positives	' 42', '-42'
0	  Pad with zeros	f"{5:03}" â†’ '005'
#	  Include base prefix	f"{255:#x}" â†’ '0xff'
